  <h2><a href="/articles/2006/05/20/link-distributed-ruby-guide">Link: Distributed Ruby Guide</a></h2>
<p class="auth">Posted by kev
<span class="typo_date" title="Sat, 20 May 2006 17:55:00 GMT">Sat, 20 May 2006 17:55:00 GMT</span></p>
<p>With <a href="http://whytheluckystiff.net/">_why</a>&#8217;s recent <a href="http://redhanded.hobix.com/cult/drbRenaissance.html">announcement</a> of the Drb Renaissance, I figured it was time to finally get my feet wet and learn about using <a href="http://www.ruby-doc.org/stdlib/libdoc/drb/rdoc/index.html">Distributed Ruby</a>.</p>

<p>Fortunately, <a href="http://www.chadfowler.com/">Chad Fowler</a> author of the fantastic <a href="http://pragmaticprogrammer.com/titles/fr_rr/index.html">Rails Recipes</a>,  has done my work for me.</p>

<p>Go check out his <a href="http://www.chadfowler.com/ruby/drb.html">guide</a> for an excellent quick read on the essentials of Drb.</p>

  
  <p class="meta">Posted in <a href="/articles/category/documentation" rel="tag">documentation</a>, <a href="/articles/category/sightings" rel="tag">sightings</a>, <a href="/articles/category/guides" rel="tag">guides</a></p>
